---
description: Stop execution immediately on test step failure and cleanup data
alwaysApply: true
---

# Test Failure Handling Policy

- If a test step fails to execute, errors out, or does not meet the pass criteria at any point during execution, you MUST STOP proceeding with the rest of the test case.
- DO NOT keep trying to work around the failure or force the test to continue.
- Immediately attempt to delete any data created during the current test run (if any).
- Mark the overall test as **Fail**.
- Document the failed step, take a screenshot of the failure state if possible, and execute the standard teardown/reporting process (e.g., calling `teardown-hook.ps1`).
